{"title":"Big Garmin Spring Sale: Fenix 8, Edge 1050, and More!","link":"https://www.dcrainmaker.com/2025/05/garmin-spring-sale-fenix-edge-endur-more.html","date":1747567002000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-720x480.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"480\" srcset=\"https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-200x133.jpeg 200w, https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://media.dcrainmaker.com/images/2025/05/Fenix8-Edge1050-720x480@2x.jpeg 1440w\" /></p>\n<p>There’s almost nothing more repeatable and predictable in Garmin’s lineup than their annual spring sale. In fact, I’d even argue it’s more predictable than their Black Friday sales. For at least a decade, Garmin’s been putting their watches and cycling gear on sale.</p>\n<p>But I’d argue, this is probably one of the best deal sets we’ve seen to date. Garmin put on sale all of their top units, including the Fenix 8 series, Edge 1050 series, inReach devices, and Forerunner devices. Oh, and Venu.</p>\n<p>Obviously, in the case of the Forerunner 265 &amp; 965, Garmin just announced the <a href=\"https://www.dcrainmaker.com/2025/05/garmin-forerunner-everything.html\">Forerunner 570</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.dcrainmaker.com/2025/05/garmin-forerunner-970-hands-on-everything-you-need-to-know.html\">Forerunner 970</a> a few days ago.  Assuming Garmin follows their recent trends, I would not expect any of the big new features to come to the FR265/965. But, I also don’t think it matters a ton. The FR965 is a great watch, and essentially unbeatable at $499 in terms of the features packed into it (including offline mapping). Of course, there are other mapping-inclusive watches cheaper, but not with as deep a feature-set as Garmin. As always, whether or not you need those other features is the real question.</p>\n<p>In any case, as for the Fenix 8, I’d assume it’ll get those handful of new Forerunner running-specific features it doesn’t yet have. I’m waiting for clarification on that, but will probably have that early Monday. I would definitely not assume a new Fenix 9 or whatever is coming soon. The absolute soonest we’d see a new Fenix would be the end of August (a 12-month cycle), but that’d be the fastest Garmin has ever iterated a Fenix variant, <a href=\"https://www.dcrainmaker.com/2023/12/garmin-fenix7-epix-release-history-explained.html\">which has never been under 13 months</a>. Point is, if you want a Fenix for the summer, get the Fenix 8 for the summer. Currently the <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Garmin-Performance-Smartwatch-Technology-Flashlight/dp/B0BYFCZZ9F?crid=3JRM2Q7R2VOJQ&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.zDpa5NuwMemQsOqfetk0ZlBB-QmrmovWExGOjTWWrIG8ZRj9bhYH15x6PCRyBKsLy6yIXGLcD5htod1EKdTSKKH1ffpA4qrEZ_r1oK9EZrZHM1ez0gHhjIWzoHhbRwTBe8wkV2KWMNQTO7IRAc9tau1UVH0xxof6OX8HBFeXykuOTKOe-JzYwffXp7XieAQfPWGdNvCbyvV9tW5DZy4ART4O7NvL_f7V0-tKCk0qDAM.OePzMRbYYhy4I4aOoBT7CrvgHV4ni1c5B8Zm5G4YOMc&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Epix%2BPro&amp;qid=1747566032&amp;sprefix=epix%2Bpro%2Caps%2C185&amp;sr=8-3&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dcr07-20&amp;linkId=a13280e08cf79cb538642c6328255bdf&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl\">Epix Pro</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Garmin-Multisport-Smartwatch-Flashlight-Capability/dp/B0BYFDZ6BM?crid=25C12NLE2RXT&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Cb9SkIfXw5rqbO-l0yrk3jQ8NtJzy4bigSkPyLAqaZF_Kk2XwWRHRzGZfMtiJVmApfjgUXjMyj2UEhYuNUiXc8TaippK0BjUAdDIruEF418MxDhL4znsajDlvGhd6NWxVq1G9yob3l_7CZcOGTDISnKrvzMT09B9reHB1kNMetLe5MopJT8lA4E04vgYzf5T5QPBcGA2B1M0EAz8MygKtvZinMKdxf-Xx7-f_BoR1u0.SiDkhVwMyirH_FnGvFntUe5w1jAdsrwjR9yYv6DgFE8&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Fenix%2B7Pro&amp;qid=1747566138&amp;sprefix=fenix%2B7pro%2Caps%2C258&amp;sr=8-3&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dcr07-20&amp;linkId=2f130ff7309f1d6c83d7caa1c564b565&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl\">Fenix 7 Pro is at $699</a>, and so I’d argue for the extra $100 to get the most current version that still gets software feature updates, but that’s just me.</p>\n<p>And of course, there’s the <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Garmin-EnduroTM-Ultraperformance-Smartwatch-Built/dp/B0DD5N9G17?crid=3JRM2Q7R2VOJQ&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.zDpa5NuwMemQsOqfetk0ZlBB-QmrmovWExGOjTWWrIG8ZRj9bhYH15x6PCRyBKsLy6yIXGLcD5htod1EKdTSKKH1ffpA4qrEZ_r1oK9EZrZHM1ez0gHhjIWzoHhbRwTBe8wkV2KWMNQTO7IRAc9tau1UVH0xxof6OX8HBFeXykuOTKOe-JzYwffXp7XieAQfPWGdNvCbyvV9tW5DZy4ART4O7NvL_f7V0-tKCk0qDAM.OePzMRbYYhy4I4aOoBT7CrvgHV4ni1c5B8Zm5G4YOMc&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Epix+Pro&amp;qid=1747566032&amp;sprefix=epix+pro%2Caps%2C185&amp;sr=8-9&amp;ufe=app_do%3Aamzn1.fos.5998aa40-ec6f-4947-a68f-cd087fee0848&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dcr07-20&amp;linkId=1bfb9a8f813a9efb5609b8cf18a1c458&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl\">Enduro 3 at $799 too on sale</a>, which is just the Fenix 8 Solar without the diving/speaker/microphone features. It continues to be the best deal there if you wanted a Fenix 8 and didn’t care about the diving/speaker/microphone features.</p>\n<p>With that, on to the deals! And thanks for supporting the site via the links below. As an Amazon Associate, I earn from qualifying purchases. Same goes for REI. Enjoy!</p>\n<h3><span>Watches &amp; Wearables:</span></h3>\n<p>This covers anything you can wear that’s watch-like or activity band-like, including sensors.</p>\n<table>\n\t<thead>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<th></th><th><span>Product</span></th><th><span>Sale Price</span></th><th><span>Amazon</span></th><th><span>Other site</span></th><th><span>Sale Notes</span></th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><a href=\"https://www.dcrainmaker.com/2024/09/apple-watch-series-10-in-depth-review.html\" target=\"_blank\"